    # (async) cleanPostObject(checkObj["id") → {any}

      1. Trims object
    1. If it has id, will delete it
    2. Gets table (only matches with values that has table)
    3. Gets keys from that table
    4. Loops through array
    5. If there is a callback passed in and the key matches the column, then it will assign that to the new object
    6. If the column type doesn't match the column value
    Parameters:
    Name Type Description
    checkObj["id" any
    Author:

    # (async) getInfo(knex, table, type) → {any}

    1. Has a dictionary -
    2. Gets knex(table).columnInfo()
    3. if property isn't created
    4. Push it into array called tableColumns
    5. If third parameter is object, will return key and value pairs of column: type. Else, if third parameter is array, will return an array of the key values
    Parameters:
    Name Type Default Description
    knex any
    table any
    type any "object"
    Author:
    • zen-out
    Returns:
    Type
    any
    Example 
    this.getTableInfo(knex, "hourglass", "object")
// returns {emails: string... }
